  "prompt": "Septoplasty at fortis?",
  "response": "If you're considering septoplasty at Fortis Hospital, it's a reputable choice. Fortis Healthcare is known for its network of hospitals with skilled ENT specialists and modern facilities. Septoplasty is a surgical procedure to correct a deviated septum, which can improve breathing difficulties and reduce nasal blockages.\n\nHere are some general steps you might consider if you're looking into this procedure at Fortis or any other hospital:\n\n1. **Consultation**: Schedule a consultation with an ENT specialist at Fortis. They will evaluate your condition and determine if septoplasty is necessary.\n\n2. **Pre-Surgical Assessment**: If septoplasty is recommended, a thorough pre-surgical assessment will be conducted. This may include imaging tests and blood work.\n\n3. **Insurance and Costs**: Inquire about the costs involved and check if your health insurance covers the procedure. Fortis staff can assist with insurance-related queries.\n\n4. **Surgery**: If the surgery is confirmed, you'll receive instructions on preparation. The procedure typically requires anesthesia and is usually done on an outpatient basis.\n\n5. **Recovery**: Post-operative care is crucial for a smooth recovery. Instructions on managing pain, preventing infection, and follow-up appointments will be provided.\n\nTo get the most accurate and updated information, it's best to contact the Fortis hospital directly where you plan to have the surgery.",
